cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a technique for vehicle detection using deep neural networks and focuses on the application of self-driving cars. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of a path planner and the evaluation of the proposed system using the hardware and software infrastructure available in the self-driving car, which suggests the category cs.RO (Robotics). The use of deep neural networks also indicates the categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed system using experimental results suggests the category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
